<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-09-17T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-09-17T15:00:00-05:00" n="494" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d494">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">860F.01/9–1445: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Ambassador in Czechoslovakia</hi>
                                (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Steinhardt</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-09-17T16:00:00-04:00">September
                                    17, 1945—4 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>230. At request of Secretary Byrnes, War Department was asked on
                            September 15 to hold up withdrawal of US forces from Zecho in order to
                            give Zecho Govt chance to ask both armies to withdraw.</p>
                        <pb facs="0505" n="493" xml:id="pg_493"/>
                        <p>This message received before arrival of Urtel 352 Sep 14.</p>
                        <p>Sent to Praha as 230; repeated to Moscow as 2018.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>